<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="002" project="spaarkeai-compose-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Spike #2 — Three-pane coordination wiring prototype</title>
    <phase>Phase 0: Spikes</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>4</estimated-hours>
    <tags>spike, frontend, typescript, prototype</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <parallel-group>A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Define and prototype the data contracts for the three-pane (Assistant ↔ Compose ↔ Context) coordination model, focusing on Flows 1, 2, and 5 per design.md §5. The deliverable is six locked TypeScript interfaces representing the six coordinated flows. Receivers may be stubs in R1 — the contracts are the load-bearing artifact, because R2+ features cannot retrofit contracts without breaking Compose. This spike unlocks Phase 2 (UI shell wiring) and is BLOCKING for any pane-coordination work.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior TypeScript / React architect comfortable designing event/message contracts across loosely-coupled UI panes, with familiarity in the SpaarkeAi three-pane shell + PaneEventBus pattern.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Six locked TypeScript interface definitions covering Flows 1–6, validated via a minimal wiring prototype that demonstrates Flows 1, 2, and 5 firing end-to-end with stub receivers. Output published as `notes/spikes/spike-2-three-pane-wiring.md`.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-working">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-context">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="task-index">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">Per design.md §5: all six flow data contracts MUST be defined and wired. Receivers may be stubs. R2 features cannot retrofit contracts after R1.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Per design.md §14 row 2: DO NOT extend `HostContext` in R1. Transient editor state (selection span, focused clause) flows as JPS scope inputs, NOT persistent session metadata.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Reuse existing PaneEventBus contract from `@spaarke/events-components` — do NOT create a parallel event bus.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Prototype code lives in `notes/spikes/` ONLY — throwaway; interfaces will be promoted to production lib in a Phase 2 task.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>typescript, pane-coordination, event-bus, three-pane-shell</topic>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/design.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-WORKSPACE-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-DASHBOARD-AND-WIDGET-MODEL.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/BUILD-A-NEW-WORKSPACE-WIDGET.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      The hardest architectural work in R1 is the wiring, not the editor. Six flows (per design.md §5) describe how the Assistant, Workspace (Compose), and Context panes coordinate. Three flows (1, 2, 5) are critical-path for R1; the other three (3, 4, 6) only need contract definitions in R1 (stubs OK). Without locked contracts up front, R2 will retrofit and break Compose. This spike's TypeScript interfaces become the single source of truth that production code in Phase 2 imports.
    </background>
    <related-work>
      <item>design.md §5 (Six coordinated flows table)</item>
      <item>design.md §14 row 2 (HostContext non-extension decision)</item>
      <item>SPAARKEAI-COMPONENT-MODEL.md (PaneEventBus contract reuse)</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context check + load knowledge">
      Verify context &lt; 70%. Read design.md §§5 + 14, SPAARKEAI-DASHBOARD-AND-WIDGET-MODEL.md, and BUILD-A-NEW-WORKSPACE-WIDGET.md. Locate the existing PaneEventBus contract in `@spaarke/events-components`.
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Scaffold prototype workspace">
      Create `notes/spikes/spike-2-prototype/` with a minimal TypeScript project (Vite + React) hosting three stub pane components (AssistantStub, ComposeStub, ContextStub) and a shared event-bus instance.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Draft six flow interfaces">
      Define TypeScript interfaces for each flow per design.md §5: WorkspaceToContextEvent, WorkspaceToAssistantEvent, ContextToWorkspaceEvent, ContextToAssistantEvent, AssistantToWorkspaceEvent, AssistantToContextEvent. Each interface specifies: payload shape, document id binding, session pointer (DocumentId), and JPS-scope-compatible selection metadata where applicable.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Wire Flows 1, 2, 5 end-to-end with stubs">
      Implement actual dispatch + receive for Flows 1 (Workspace→Context), 2 (Workspace→Assistant), 5 (Assistant→Workspace). Receivers log to console and update minimal UI state. Verify event payloads round-trip via the bus.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Validate against design.md §14 row 2">
      Confirm no flow interface persists transient state into HostContext. All selection/span metadata is payload-only, consumed and discarded.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Author final interface file">
      Produce `notes/spikes/spike-2-prototype/contracts.ts` as the single locked-interface artifact. Add JSDoc on every interface explaining R1 vs R2 receiver expectations.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Write spike report">
      Write `notes/spikes/spike-2-three-pane-wiring.md` with: prototype location, interface file path, decision rationale per flow, stub vs runtime behavior matrix, and what Phase 2 must do to promote contracts to production lib.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Update TASK-INDEX + close">
      Update `projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 002 as ✅. Update `current-task.md`. Report completion.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="npm">Vite + React + TypeScript prototype</tool>
    <tool name="git">Version control</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="prototype" ephemeral="true">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/notes/spikes/spike-2-prototype/</output>
    <output type="contracts" ephemeral="true">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/notes/spikes/spike-2-prototype/contracts.ts</output>
    <output type="report">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/notes/spikes/spike-2-three-pane-wiring.md</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (status update)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All six flow interfaces are defined in `contracts.ts` with explicit payload shapes + JSDoc.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Flows 1, 2, 5 fire end-to-end through the prototype event bus with stub receivers logging payloads.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No interface persists transient editor state into HostContext (per design.md §14 row 2).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Spike report names which contracts are R1-runtime vs R1-stub vs R2-runtime per receiver.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">TASK-INDEX.md status for task 002 is ✅ and the spike report is committed.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
  </execution>
</task>
